An '''Opele''' (spelled '''Ocuele''' in [[Latin America]]) is a divination chain used in [[Traditional African religion|traditional African]] and [[Afro-American religions]], notably in [[If<U+00E1>]] and [[Yoruba religion|Yoruba tradition]].

A [[Babalawo]] (diviner) uses the Opele in order to communicate with the spirits who are able to identify the causes and solutions to personal and collective problems and restore harmony with the spirits.

